Reese Witherspoon is in talks with MGM to reprise her role as Elle Woods in "Legally Blonde 3."
Witherspoon would also produce through her Hello Sunshine production company, if the deal goes through, Reuters reported.
"Legally Blonde" was a success for MGM, grossing $141.8 million worldwide.
"Legally Blonde" also starred Luke Wilson, Selma Blair, Matthew Davis, Victor Garber, and Jennifer Coolidge.
MGM also released 2003's "Legally Blonde 2: Red, White & Blonde," set in Washington, D.C.